  "homeTip_progressive_overload": "Add a little more weight or one more rep each week. That's how you grow.",
  "homeTip_protein_per_meal": "Aim for 30–40g of protein per meal. Spreading it out beats one big dose.",
  "homeTip_sleep_for_recovery": "Your muscles don't grow during the workout — they grow while you sleep.",
  "homeTip_walk_after_meals": "A 10-minute walk after eating can cut your blood sugar spike by 30%.",
  "homeTip_hydration_basics": "Drink half your bodyweight in ounces daily. Add more on training days.",
  "homeTip_warm_up_matters": "5 minutes of movement prep makes every set safer and stronger.",
  "homeTip_compound_lifts": "Squat, hinge, push, pull, carry. Master those five and you've covered 80%.",
  "homeTip_rest_days_grow_muscle": "Rest days aren't laziness — they're when the adaptation actually happens.",
  "homeTip_form_over_weight": "Ego lifts with bad form build injury, not muscle. Dial in the movement first.",
  "homeTip_track_to_progress": "If you're not tracking it, you're not managing it. Log your sets.",
  "homeTip_mind_muscle_connection": "Slow down and feel the muscle working. It's not just about moving weight.",
  "homeTip_deload_week": "Every 4–6 weeks, cut volume by 40%. Your body will come back stronger.",
  "homeTip_eat_before_training": "Training fasted can work, but a small meal 60–90 min before helps most people perform better.",
  "homeTip_creatine_basics": "Creatine monohydrate is the most studied supplement in sports science. 3–5g daily works.",
  "homeTip_breathing_during_lifts": "Exhale on the hard part, inhale on the easy part. Brace your core throughout.",
  "homeTip_consistency_beats_perfection": "Showing up at 70% is better than skipping because you can't give 100%.",
  "homeTip_set_rep_ranges": "1–5 reps builds strength. 6–12 builds size. 12–20 builds endurance. All matter.",
  "homeTip_eccentric_focus": "The lowering phase is where most muscle damage (and growth) happens. Control it.",
  "homeTip_fiber_and_gut": "30g of fiber a day keeps energy steady and reduces cravings. Most people get 15.",
  "homeTip_caffeine_timing": "Caffeine peaks 45–60 min after drinking. Time it before your session.",
  "homeTip_rate_of_perceived_exertion": "Rate your effort 1–10. Staying between 7–8 most sessions is the sweet spot.",
  "homeTip_stress_and_recovery": "High stress = high cortisol = slower recovery. Manage the whole picture.",
  "homeTip_meal_timing_simple": "Eat mostly whole foods, hit your protein, sleep enough. Most of the rest is noise.",
  "homeTip_core_in_every_lift": "Your core is working on every compound movement. You don't need 20 minutes of crunches.",
  "homeTip_mobility_daily": "10 minutes of mobility work daily beats a 60-minute session once a week.",
  "homeTip_cardio_and_strength": "Cardio doesn't kill gains if you're eating enough and not overdoing volume.",
  "homeTip_sodium_and_water": "Salt isn't the enemy — it helps with hydration and performance. Don't fear it.",
  "homeTip_omega3_basics": "1–2g EPA+DHA daily reduces inflammation and supports joint health.",
  "homeTip_vitamin_d": "Most people are deficient in vitamin D. 1000–2000 IU daily is a safe baseline.",
  "homeTip_grip_strength": "Grip strength predicts longevity better than almost any other metric. Train it.",
  "homeTip_no_junk_volume": "10 hard, focused sets beat 20 half-hearted ones. Quality over quantity.",
  "homeTip_split_options": "Push/pull/legs, upper/lower, full-body 3x — all work if you're consistent.",
  "homeTip_tempo_training": "Try a 3-0-1 tempo (3s down, 0 pause, 1s up) to feel any exercise differently.",
  "homeTip_cold_exposure": "Cold showers or ice baths may blunt post-workout inflammation. Save them for after, not before.",
  "homeTip_periodization": "Vary your rep ranges and intensity over time. Linear progress doesn't last forever.",
  "homeTip_ankle_mobility": "Limited ankle mobility forces compensations in squats. Stretch and drill it daily.",
  "homeTip_zone2_cardio": "Zone 2 cardio (conversational pace) builds the aerobic base everything else sits on.",
  "homeTip_scale_not_everything": "Weight fluctuates 2–4 lbs daily from water and food. Judge by weekly averages.",
  "homeTip_compound_before_isolation": "Do your big lifts first when you're fresh. Isolation work comes at the end.",
  "homeTip_protein_sources_vary": "Mix protein sources — chicken, eggs, Greek yogurt, legumes. Variety covers all amino acids.",
